quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  17,78,"Establish prayer at the decline of the sun until the darkness of the night, and the recitation of dawn [prayer], for the recitation of dawn is ever witnessed [by the angles]"
  17,79,"And wake up during the night and pray, as an additional prayer for you [O Prophet], so your Lord may raise you to a praised status [of Grand Intercession]"
  17,80,"And say, “My Lord, make me enter an honorable entrance and make me exit an honorable exit, and grant me from Yourself a supporting authority.”"
  17,81,"And say, “The truth has come and falsehood has perished. Indeed, falsehood is bound to perish.”"
  17,82,"We send down the Qur’an as a healing and mercy for the believers, but it does not increase the wrongdoers except in loss"
  17,83,"When We bestow favor upon man, he turns away and distances himself, but when evil befalls him, he is in utter despair"
  17,84,"Say, “Everyone acts in his own way, but your Lord knows best whose way is best guided.”"